Number 1416
Name Lounge, Converted 
REGION 204
CHANNEL 2041
DEEPCAVE
MONSTER_GROUP 88
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
At one time, this may have been a comfortable lounge. Why it is where it is,
however, is a mystery.  Presently, however, there are a few spoiled paintings
on the walls and the skeletons of a few couches and not much else.  In the
northeast corner, the one furthest from the hallways on the north and south
walls, there are scraps of cloth that resembles a fairly large bed or nest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1415
EXIT S 1417
ITEM 0 1305
EXTEND 0 whose framework is all that's left
ITEM 1 1305
EXTEND 1 that has a few scraps of fabric left
ITEM 2 468
EXTEND 2 made of material from the couches
;
Number 1417
Name L-Shaped Corridor
REGION 204
CHANNEL 2041
DEEPCAVE
MONSTER_GROUP 88
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This hallway is no more than fifty feet in total length, bent in a right angle
halfway down its length to go both north and east.  At each end is a room that
is in disrepair.  There are no visible braces in this hallway, although the
surrounding walls seem to indicate that it was made from solid rock.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1416
EXIT E 1418
;
Number 1418
Name Small Room
REGION 204
CHANNEL 2041
DEEPCAVE
MONSTER_GROUP 88
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This area seems to be some sort of a office, or it used to be.  A desk and
chair are facing the opening on the east wall, and slightly protecting the
hallway on the west wall.  Neither the desk, nor the chair appear to be
usable either now nor ever again.
*DESCRIPTION_END
